      • getJsonResource

        public <T> T getJsonResource(java.lang.String path,
                             java.lang.Class<T> classOfT)
                      throws java.io.FileNotFoundException,
                             java.io.IOException
        Reads a json resource file and returns the object.
        Parameters:
        path - path to the resource file.
        classOfT - the type of object to be converted from json.
        Returns:
        an object of type T, converted from json.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an I/O exception occurs while reading the file.
        java.io.FileNotFoundException - if the file cannot be found.
        java.lang.OutOfMemoryError - if the file is too large.
        JsonSyntaxException - if the json is not a valid representation of classOfT.
        java.nio.file.InvalidPathException - if the path to the file is invalid.
        java.lang.SecurityException - if the file cannot be accessed.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if an argument is null.
